+# DEC-V61-047 Round 2 — Codex Consolidated Verdict
+
+**Overall**: CHANGES_REQUIRED
+**Blockers**: 0
+**Expert verdict**: CHANGES_REQUIRED — F1/F2/F5/F6 are substantively closed and F3 deferral is acceptable, but F4 is not fully closed because `naca0012_airfoil` now teaches the wrong authoritative setup (`Re=6e6`, `α≈4°`) on the new student-facing solver card while repo truth remains `Re=3e6`, `α=0°`.
+**Novice verdict**: CHANGES_REQUIRED — Story tab is much more learnable now, but a novice can still leave with the wrong airfoil benchmark setup on a core case, so I cannot call the suite textbook-grade yet.
+
+## Remediation verification
+- F1 [verify]: CLOSED — visual-only Story copy no longer hardcodes FAIL. The branch now says `Tier C · 过程证据，未做自动化金标准比对` and explicitly says it is neither pass nor fail in `ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1641-1658`. Backend visual-only context also returns `verdict: None` in `ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py:329-387`. This matters because both `circular_cylinder_wake` and `plane_channel_flow` fixtures still declare `expected_verdict: PASS` in `ui/backend/tests/fixtures/runs/circular_cylinder_wake/audit_real_run_measurement.yaml:8-18` and `ui/backend/tests/fixtures/runs/plane_channel_flow/audit_real_run_measurement.yaml:8-18`. In an isolated export of `10a3463`, `grep -n "FAIL" ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx | head -5` only hit status-map/comment usages, not a visual-only hardcoded FAIL.
+- F2 [verify]: CLOSED — `RunResidualsCard` now tries the real `audit_real_run/renders/residuals.png` first, then only falls back to the synthetic SVG after `onError`, with explicit `⚠ 示意图 · illustrative only` copy and `收敛不等于"算对"` framing in `ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1267-1319`. Isolated verification on exported `10a3463`: `npm run typecheck` passed, and `npm run build` passed with a production bundle (`dist/assets/index-CPO9gUxS.js 817.75 kB / gzip 267.94 kB`).
+- F5 [verify]: CLOSED — `turbulent_flat_plate` now teaches laminar Blasius in `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:112-136`, matching gold's laminar correction, `Cf=0.664/sqrt(Re_x)`, and `ref_value=0.00420` at x=0.5 in `knowledge/gold_standards/turbulent_flat_plate.yaml:5-36`. `plane_channel_flow` is now honestly framed as a disguised incompatibility sample in `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:139-162`, matching gold's `INCOMPATIBLE_WITH_LITERATURE_DISGUISED_AS_COMPATIBLE` contract in `knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:7-27`, including the emitter math being numerically self-consistent but physics-wrong in `src/plane_channel_uplus_emitter.py:246-292`. `impinging_jet` now teaches the two-layer gap in `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:165-187`, matching gold's `empty`-not-`wedge` plus A4 iteration-cap hazards in `knowledge/gold_standards/impinging_jet.yaml:8-28`. `differential_heated_cavity` now teaches the `Ra=1e6` de Vahl Davis benchmark in `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:232-250`, matching the downgraded gold regime in `knowledge/gold_standards/differential_heated_cavity.yaml:5-25`.
+- F4 [verify]: PARTIAL — the new `CFD 全流程` section is correctly added as a 2-column responsive 4-card layout on Story in `ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:406-440`, and `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts` now contains all 4 new fields for all 10 cases (`grep -cE "solver_setup_zh|mesh_strategy_zh|boundary_conditions_zh|observable_extraction_zh"` on exported `10a3463` returned `44`). The cards are concrete for multiple spot-checks. `lid_driven_cavity` names `simpleFoam`, `ncx=ncy=40`, moving-wall/no-slip BCs, and `x=0.5` centerline extraction in `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:49-67`, aligning with `knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:96-108`. `circular_cylinder_wake` correctly points to transient `pimpleFoam` plus FFT extraction in `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:106-109`, aligning with `src/cylinder_strouhal_fft.py:1-35`. But `naca0012_airfoil`'s new solver card is factually wrong: it says `Re=6e6` and `α≈4°` in `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:205`, while whitelist, gold, adapter notes, and reference fixture all still anchor the case at `Re=3e6`, `angle_of_attack=0.0` in `knowledge/whitelist.yaml:234-247`, `knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:5-29`, `src/foam_agent_adapter.py:6370-6376`, and `ui/backend/tests/fixtures/runs/naca0012_airfoil/reference_pass_measurement.yaml:1-19`. Because F4's goal was a student-facing reproducibility path, this drift means F4 is not fully closed.
+- F6 [verify]: CLOSED — `PhysicsContractPanel` now keeps `condition` and `如果不满足：...` visible while collapsing raw `evidence_ref` into `<details>` in `ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:602-625`. For `impinging_jet`, this is the right novice UX: the student sees the teachable consequence first, while `empty/wedge`, A4, and adapter/file-path jargon stay opt-in, matching the raw evidence load in `knowledge/gold_standards/impinging_jet.yaml:11-27`.
+
+## Deferral judgment
+- F3: accept — the backend Tier-C gap is still real. `comparison_report.py` still keeps 9 cases in `_VISUAL_ONLY_CASES`, returns `verdict=None`, and skips gold-overlay / metrics / GCI assembly in `ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py:45-60`, `ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py:329-387`, and `ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py:422-424`. Tests still encode that visual-only HTML/PDF should not render full reports in `ui/backend/tests/test_comparison_report_visual_only.py:74-111` and `ui/backend/tests/test_comparison_report_visual_only.py:164-212`. I also reran that isolated backend file on exported `10a3463`, and it passed `10/10`. But after F1/F2/F4/F5/F6, the frontend Story tab now provides an honest novice teaching path, so the missing Tier-B overlay is backlog, not the thing that should fail this round.
+
+## New findings (if any)
+- N1 🟠 `naca0012_airfoil` new F4 teaching card teaches the wrong authoritative setup. `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:205` says `Re=6e6` and `α≈4°`, but repo truth is `Re=3e6`, `α=0°` in `knowledge/whitelist.yaml:244-247`, `knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:5-29`, `src/foam_agent_adapter.py:6371-6372`, and `ui/backend/tests/fixtures/runs/naca0012_airfoil/reference_pass_measurement.yaml:1-19`. This is pedagogy-facing correctness drift on a core case, not a copy-style nit.
+
+## If CHANGES_REQUIRED: round-3 directive
+- Minimum fix: edit `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:205-208` so the `naca0012_airfoil` teaching cards match authoritative repo truth. Replace `Re=6e6` with `Re=3e6`, replace `α≈4°` with `α=0°` (or otherwise explain that the canonical benchmark here is zero-angle attached flow), and keep the near-surface-vs-exact-surface Cp extraction caveat aligned with `knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:15-28`.
+- After that targeted fix, this review should not reopen F3. Minimum reruns: `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`, and `PYTHONPATH=. /Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/.venv/bin/pytest ui/backend/tests/test_comparison_report_visual_only.py -q`.

